The paper deals with network pruning and sparsity learning in deep neural networks, which are topics related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The experiments are conducted on image classification datasets, indicating a focus on computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper introduces a generic mechanism that can be adapted for any type of architecture, which suggests a broader scope and could potentially fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
